3. FFmpeg — fetched at runtime, not bundled
-------------------------------------------
Homepage: https://ffmpeg.org
Used by:  src/tamlil/util.py (ffmpeg_path / ffprobe_path) and
          src/tamlil/denoise.py (arnndn / aresample / highpass filters)

Tamlil does not include an FFmpeg binary in this repository. The static-ffmpeg
package (see below) downloads one to the local machine on first use, and Tamlil
invokes it as a separate program via subprocess. Tamlil neither links against
FFmpeg nor redistributes the binary.

License and build variant. FFmpeg's own code is dual-licensed: the core is
LGPL-2.1-or-later, but a build that enables GPL-only components becomes
GPL-2.0-or-later as a whole. The build fetched by static-ffmpeg 3.0 (from
https://github.com/zackees/ffmpeg_bins) is a GPL build: its reported
configuration includes `--enable-gpl` together with GPL-only components
(libx264, libx265, libvidstab, postproc) and does NOT include `--enable-nonfree`
(so it remains redistributable under the GPL). Treat the fetched FFmpeg binary
as GPL-2.0-or-later.

Obligation. Because Tamlil calls FFmpeg as a separate program and does not
distribute it, the GPL's copyleft does not extend to Tamlil's own
Apache-2.0-licensed code. Anyone who chooses to redistribute the fetched FFmpeg
binary must comply with the GPL, including making the corresponding source
available. FFmpeg's complete source is at https://ffmpeg.org and
https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg.


